# Testing Rules

- Every behavior change must include or update automated tests.
- API domain rules should be covered with ExUnit unit tests (`mix test`).
- API contracts and authorization paths should be covered with integration/controller tests.
- For Phoenix endpoints, test both valid and invalid payloads with clear status assertions.
- For state-machine logic, include invalid transition tests in addition to happy paths.
- Prefer `ConnCase`/`DataCase` style organization for maintainable backend tests.
- Frontend components should be tested with Testing Library-style behavior tests.
- Critical frontend flows must have Playwright end-to-end coverage.
- Keep frontend verification order explicit: `install -> typecheck -> lint -> unit tests -> e2e`.
- Keep unit tests and Playwright E2E isolated; never run Playwright specs via Bun unit test command.
- After dependency upgrades, run a full verification pass and resolve compatibility issues before closing an increment.
- Test success, error, and edge states (not just happy paths).
- Keep tests deterministic; avoid hidden inter-test coupling and timing flakiness.
- Update test docs/commands in `README.md` when introducing new test suites.
- Keep Gherkin coverage in sync with ExUnit test cases:
  - API controller test names must be represented in `api/test/features/controller_regression_coverage.feature`.
  - API domain/context test names must be represented in `api/test/features/domain_regression_coverage.feature`.
  - When adding/renaming/removing API tests, update the corresponding feature coverage matrix in the same change.
